column145:
Apollo Global Management incorporates ESG issues into its investment analysis and decision-making processes. It reports on its ESG activities to its clients, and supports the implementation of ESG practices in the investment management industry. 

Formalized in 2008, Apollo's RI Program is based on three pillars: thorough diligence of ESG risks, meaningful engagement with portfolio companies post-acquisition and annual reporting of both quantitative and qualitative ESG metrics. 

Apollo asks portfolio companies to report on more than 30 quantitative ESG key performance indicators. As of December 2018, over 120 portfolio companies have participated in Apollo's ESG Reporting Program.
